_:N90979795dd79472a910f5acf2b02949e <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Richard was appointed as a Director General in the Office of the Parliamentary Counsel in November 2025. His team of drafters is responsible for delivering primary legislation for the following Departments:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Energy Security &amp; Net Zero;</li>\n  <li>Transport;</li>\n  <li>Education;</li>\n  <li>Science, Innovation &amp; Technology;</li>\n  <li>Environment, Food &amp; Rural Affairs. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>While at OPC he has drafted Bills on a wide range of areas, including energy, elections, cybersecurity, education, transport, the armed forces and public service pensions. He was seconded to Cabinet Office Legal Advisers in 2019-20, advising on cross-Whitehall devolution matters (in particular in the context of coronavirus and EU exit). He also spent two years at HMRC’s Tax Law Rewrite Project (2006-8) as part of the drafting team dealing with the rewrite of corporation tax legislation.</p>\n\n<p>Before joining OPC, Richard qualified as a solicitor at Slaughter and May, where he practised in one of the firm’s general corporate departments.</p>\n" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
