<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/richard-spitz> <http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml/vocab#license> <https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/doc/open-government-licence/version/3/> <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/rdfa> .
<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/richard-spitz> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "Richard was appointed as a Director General in the Office of the Parliamentary Counsel in November 2025. His team of drafters is responsible for delivering primary legislation for the following Departments: Energy Security & Net Zero; Transport; Education; Science, Innovation & Technology; Environment, Food & Rural Affairs.  While at OPC he has drafted Bills on a wide range of areas, including energy, elections, cybersecurity, education, transport, the armed forces and public service pensions. He was seconded to Cabinet Office Legal Advisers in 2019-20, advising on cross-Whitehall devolution matters (in particular in the context of coronavirus and EU exit). He also spent two years at HMRC’s Tax Law Rewrite Project (2006-8) as part of the drafting team dealing with the rewrite of corporation tax legislation. Before joining OPC, Richard qualified as a solicitor at Slaughter and May, where he practised in one of the firm’s general corporate departments."@en <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/rdfa> .
